<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-403-318  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 403 318.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  July 1989 v14 n7 p259(8).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The Qsim simulation toolkit. (includes related article on stringand variable construction in C)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kimbrell, Roy E.; Corell, Linda; Bass, RObert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Qsim, a custom-designed toolkit for modeling both computer andreal-world systems, is described.andP;  A custom, user-written set oftools provides a better understanding of the operations of modelsand better control over the modeling process.andP;  Qsim's tools aredesigned to create queuing system models but can be adapted toother types of models by combining them with various modelingtechniques.andP;  Building a model consists of identifying the basicprocesses in the system, selecting the modeling tools for eachprocess, and developing new tools for processes not yetcategorized.andP;  The Qsim Toolkit produces models similar toprogramming-language interpreters.andP;  Examples of models developedwith the Qsim Toolkit are presented.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ModelingSimulation of Computer SystemsTutorialApplications ProgrammingUser-Written Software.andO;Feature:   illustrationchartprogram.andO;Caption:   The simulation model is a queue system (chart)The output from Qsim Toolkit (program)The C language source code using the Qsim Toolkit for the example(program)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>